In both scenarios, bidding ''Low'' yields a better or equal outcome for you. It is the **dominant strategy**. A perfectly rational competitor will reason the same way, leading to both parties bidding ''Low'' and ending up with $2M each, even though a cooperative ''High-High'' bid would have been more profitable for both.', 15, 180, ARRAY['game_theory', 'prisoners_dilemma', 'strategy', 'sales', 'negotiation']::text[], ARRAY['game theory', 'dominant strategy', 'prisoner''s dilemma', 'pricing']::text[], NULL, NULL, NULL, true, 'user-1754047814104-568ee9dw7'),
